ğŸ” 9. IAM & permission failures (very common)

Typical failures:
Pod cannot access S3, SQS, Secrets Manager
AccessDenied errors

Validate:
Is IRSA used?
Is service account annotated?
Is trust policy correct?

kubectl get sa <sa> -o yaml
ğŸ‘‰ One missing annotation can cause a full outage.
ğŸ“¦ 10. ConfigMap / Secret issues

Symptoms:
App starts but behaves wrongly
App cannot read config
Checks:

kubectl describe pod <pod>
kubectl get cm
kubectl get secret

Look for:
Wrong key
Wrong mount path
Wrong namespace

ğŸ“ˆ 11. High latency but CPU and memory are normal

Experienced engineers check:

Downstream dependency latency
DB connection pool exhaustion
Thread pool limits
Ingress network hops
TLS handshake overhead
ğŸ‘‰ Metrics alone never explain latency.
 You must inspect the request path.
